Sixty-six people have tested positive at the hospital and 48 of those are staff members. DURBAN - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has expressed concern about St. Augustine's Hospital in Durban. Sixty-six people have tested positive at the hospital and 48 of those are staff members. READ: COVID-19 death toll rises to 13, confirmed cases to 1,749 Mkhize said government was negotiating with hospital management "with the view to close it down". "We have said they must stop taking any new outpatients and inpatients," Mkhize said. Nursing union Denosa has also slammed the hospital for allegedly not protecting its staff. The union says staff members are made to work without personhttps://www.enca.com/news/netcare-ceo-denies-covid-19-doctor-was-required-go-back-workal protective equipment. READ: Health Minister receives 200,000 PPEs from Motsepe Foundation The hospital has however denied the allegations. South Africa has reported 13 deaths so far. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. - Additional reporting AFP